Rotary District 6040 is with Marc Horner.

What a wonderful day. Long drive to my club visit today. Saw my friends in Unionville, MO. They have gotten a lot more snow than we have. Very enjoyable visit. Saw the mural and the plans for their pocket park District project. When the snow melts it will be great. Saw the library where their People of Action award winning project took place last year. Delivered last year’s Rotary Citation to IPP Tom. Had a nice visit with AG Joel and President Clint. Makes you excited to be a Rotarian when you see the impact they are making in their community. #Rotaryinspires

post_text: Join the fun October 19 for Rotary Trivia. The questions are not encyclopedia type questions. Categories and sample questions from our last event were: Geography (What is the capitol of S. Dakota?), PC Trivia (Henry Clay Dean's homestead in eastern Putnam County was named __?), Name the Classic TV show - theme songs of classic TV shows were played (Cheers, MASH, Bewitched), Current Events (What country recently legalized the recreational use of marijuana?), Spelling (hierarchy, cemetery, zucchini), Brown Bag - each team received 10 beans to identify (coffee, lima, pinto), Cooking (how many items in a Baker's Dozen?), National Football League (What player has the most Super Bowl appearances?), Classic Cars - a sheet of classic car taillights was handed out to identify (Corvette, Ford LTD, DeLorean, Pacer), Movie Music - songs from movies were played (Rocky, Bridge of the River Kwai)

Joel Pratt Thomas Keedy Jim Garrett Michele Pettengill Stafford Peggy Hart Ron Stuckey Jane Blackburn Clint Stobbe
shared_text:
Rotary District 6040
April 18, 2019 at 10:27 AM ·

Attention Shoes Enthusiasts of District 6040 - Please take a look at this thank-you message from Dickson Masindano, the Executive Director of Buckner Kenya. We send shoes to Kenya every year that include D6040 collections, but this year our caravan (coming up next week!) is specifically highlighting Kenya. He’s thanking our District all for all of the shoes we have sent in the past, and for all of the shoes we will collect this year. Please note -there is a huge danger of jigger parasites for children in Kenya, so the shoes we collect this year will not only send children to school but they will also keep their feet clean, healthy, and free from jiggers. Let's make this shoe drive the best so far! #PeopleofAction; #TogetherWeTransform

post_text: It was one year ago today that Craig A Comstock and I were in a plane crash. Craig's life was saved in part from the 5 units of whole blood and 4 units of plasma he received that evening. This life-saving blood was donated by people like you and I, taking an hour out of their day to help others. We are so grateful! The next drive in Unionville is Monday, July 23. If you are able to donate, take a few minutes to either call 800-733-2767 or go online to redcrossblood.org to schedule your blood donation. Thank you!

post_text: Rotarian Kevin Collins updated us last week on the hay delivery area residents had made. This is the next step to help those who have been burned out.
shared_text:
Omaha Baptist Church
March 28, 2017 at 1:46 PM ·

Prairie Fire Assistance
A fencing crew from Omaha Baptist Church will travel to Ashland, KS, site of recent prairie fires that destroyed over one million acres in Texas, Colorado, Oklahoma, and Kansas. The fire also took 10,000 head of cattle and seven human lives. The crew will leave Tuesday morning, April 4 and spend four days working with a rancher north of Ashland. Donations of fence posts and barbed wire will be accepted and taken to Kansas. The fence posts need to be new 6’ T-posts and the wire standard four-point 12 ½ guage (heavy) wire. Goober’s General Store at Hartford and MFA in Unionville will be the collection points. Look for flat-bed trailers and place items on the trailers. Contact Kevin Collins @ 660) 216-3465 for more information.

post_text: Mike May spoke to Rotary about his experiences with polio. He contracted polio in his arm and shoulder as a 7 year old, but recovered and later threw a no-hitter in a Little League baseball game at age 13. Mike is shown with his wife Carol and foundation chair Joel Pratt. Rotary has been a big player in the eradication of polio since 1979. Polio is left in only three countries - Afghanistan, Pakistan and Nigeria.

post_text: Work has begun on the restoration of the building south of the library. Tim Sizemore and his crew pulled in today and have already removed a truck load of old brick. The wall will be taken down, the foundation repaired, and a new wall will be constructed that will help stablize the facade. Donation checks should be made payable to the Friends of the Library and mailed to Unionville Rotary at PO Box 64, Unionville, MO 63565

post_text: Unionville Rotary is excited to partner with the Friends of the Library and the PC Library Board in the "Preserving the Past, Building the Future" project. The old Community Action Agency building which adjoins the library on the south will be restored and then opened up for a library expansion. Various fundraising events will be held in the coming months to raise needed funds.

post_text: Unionville Rotary will be giving away our raffle prize February 18 at the varsity basketball game. The winner has a choice of: $1,000, a 4-day Caribbean cruise for 2, an Amtrak Western Rail Journey, or a 60-inch LED flat screen TV. Tickets are $10 and will be sold at the next three varsity basketball games. Proceeds support the youth of our community.
